SEC. 101. (a) The objective of this Act is to restore and main­tain the chemical, physical, and biological integrity of the Nation’s waters. In order to achieve this objective it is hereby declared that, consistent with the provisions of this Act—
* it is the national goal that the discharge of pollutants into the navigable waters be eliminated by 1985;
* it is the national goal that wherever attainable, an inÂ­terim goal of water quality which provides for the protection and propagation of fish, shellfish, and wildlife and provides for recreation in and on the water be achieved by July 1, 1983;
* it is the national policy that the discharge of toxic polÂ­lutants in toxic amounts be prohibited;
* it is the national policy that Federal financial assistÂ­ance be provided to construct publicly owned waste treatment works;
* it is the national policy that areawide treatment manÂ­agement planning processes be developed and implemented to assure adequate control of sources of pollutants in each State;
* it is the national policy that a major research and demÂ­onstration effort be made to develop technology necessary to eliminate the discharge of pollutants into the navigable waters, waters of the contiguous zone and the oceans; and
* it is the national policy that programs for the control of nonpoint sources of pollution be developed and implemented in an expeditious manner so as to enable the goals of this Act to be met through the control of both point and nonpoint sources of pollution.

